The paper deals with the problem of pre-processing an array to efficiently answer range maximum queries in two dimensions. This is a classic problem in data structures and falls under the category of computational geometry and data structures (cs.CG). The paper also focuses on determining the effective entropy of the array, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of entropy and information theory is also related to coding theory (cs.CC). The paper uses probabilistic analysis to derive bounds on the expected effective entropy, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes data structures to answer queries efficiently, which is related to data structures (cs.DS).
